query:
All of the triangles in the figure and the central hexagon are equilateral. Given that $\overline{AC}$ is 3 units long, how many square units, expressed in simplest radical form, are in the area of the entire star? [asy]
import olympiad; import geometry; import graph; size(150); defaultpen(linewidth(0.8));
pair[] vertices;
for(int i = 0; i < 6; ++i){

vertices[i] = dir(30 + 60*i);
}
draw(vertices[0]--vertices[2]--vertices[4]--cycle);
draw(vertices[1]--vertices[3]--vertices[5]--cycle);
label("$D$",vertices[0],NE); label("$C$",vertices[1],N); label("$B$",vertices[2],NW); label("$A$",vertices[3],SW);
label("$F$",vertices[4],S); label("$E$",vertices[5],SE);
[/asy]

ground_truth:
We divide the hexagon into six equilateral triangles, which are congruent by symmetry.  The star is made up of 12 of these triangles.    [asy]
pair A,B,C,D,E,F;
real x=sqrt(3);
F=(0,0);
E=(x,1);
D=(x,3);
C=(0,4);
A=(-x,1);
B=(-x,3);
draw(A--C--E--cycle); draw(B--D--F--cycle);
label("$D$",D,NE); label("$C$",C,N); label("$B$",B,NW); label("$A$",A,SW);
label("$F$",F,S); label("$E$",E,SE);
draw((1/x,1)--(-1/x,3)); draw((-1/x,1)--(1/x,3)); draw((2/x,2)--(-2/x,2));
[/asy] Let the side length of each triangle be $s$. $AC$ is made up of three triangle side lengths, so we have $3s=3 \Rightarrow s = 1$.  Thus, each triangle has area $\frac{1^2 \sqrt{3}}{4}$ and the star has area $12\cdot \frac{1^2 \sqrt{3}}{4} = \boxed{3\sqrt{3}}$.

